    {
      "number": 1,
      "id": "I_kwDOTKjSMc8AAAABHz4qYQ",
      "title": "What triggers policy updates?",
      "url": "https://github.com/mirjak/draft-happy-qlog/issues/1",
      "state": "OPEN",
      "author": "mirjak",
      "authorAssociation": "OWNER",
      "assignees": [],
      "labels": [],
      "body": "The config_set event includes \"network_change\" as a reason for policy updates. However, HEv3 does not explicitly define a\n  mechanism where the configurable policy values (delays, preferred family, etc.) change in response to a network event.\n\nHEv3 mentions network changes in the context of:\n - Flushing historical data when the device changes networks (Section 5.3)\n - Enabling IPv6-only/NAT64 features on IPv6-mostly networks (Section 8)\n\nBut these are behavioral adaptations within a fixed policy, not policy parameter changes.\n\nShould \"network_change\" remain as a config_set reason in this qlog schema, or should it be left to the HEv3 spec to define if/when policy changes in response to network events? Do we need other reasons?",
      "createdAt": "2026-07-06T12:30:20Z",
      "updatedAt": "2026-07-06T12:30:20Z",
      "closedAt": null,
      "comments": []
    },
